【Analysis】According to the problem, we can set the number of each weight as an unknown, with 19-gram beads having $x$ pieces and 17-gram beads having $y$ pieces, and then list the relationship, taking values step by step within the range of positive integers, and finally find the values that meet the requirements.

【Solution】Solution: According to the analysis, let there be $x$ 19-gram beads and $y$ 17-gram beads, then:
$19 x+17 y=2017$, and since $x, y$ are both positive integers,
$\therefore 1 \leqslant x \leqslant \frac{2017-17 \times 1}{19}=\frac{2000}{19}<106, \quad 1 \leqslant y \leqslant \frac{2017-19 \times 1}{17}=\frac{1996}{17}<118$;
$19 x+17 y=2017 \Rightarrow x=\frac{2017-17 y}{19}$, by the remainder theorem, to make $x$ a positive integer, $2017-17 y$ must be divisible by 19,

i.e., the remainder is 0, and 2017 divided by 19 has a remainder of 3, so $17 y$ divided by 19 also has a remainder of 3, among all numbers that have a remainder of 3 when divided by 19, are less than 2017, and can be divided by 17, there are only:
(1) 136, i.e., $17 y=136 \Rightarrow y=8, x=\frac{2017-17 \times 8}{19}=99, x+y=99+8=107$;
(2) 459, i.e., $17 y=459 \Rightarrow y=27, x=\frac{2017-459}{19}=82, x+y=82+27=109$;
(3) 782, i.e., $17 y=782 \Rightarrow y=46, x=\frac{2017-782}{19}=65, x+y=65+46=111$;
(4) 1105, i.e., $17 y=1105 \Rightarrow y=65, x=\frac{2017-1105}{19}=48, x+y=48+65=113$;
(5) 1428, i.e., $17 y=1428 \Rightarrow y=84, x=\frac{2017-1428}{19}=31, x+y=31+84=115$;
(6) 1751, i.e., $17 y=1751 \Rightarrow y=103, x=\frac{2017-1751}{19}=14, x+y=14+103=117$.

In summary, the possible values of the sum of the two types of beads, i.e., $x+y$, are: 107, 109, 111, 113, 115, 117.
Therefore, the answer is: 107, 109, 111, 113, 115, 117.

