(vi) Let $(a, m)=1, k \geqslant 1$, then from $a^{k} \equiv b^{k}(\bmod m), a^{k+1} \equiv$ $b^{k+1}(\bmod m)$ both hold, it can be deduced that $a \equiv b(\bmod m)$.

